Movie (Norm)
'Awvea ultxari ohengeyä, Nawma Sa'nok lrrtok siveiyi.
'awve/adj ultxa/n ohenga/pn nawm/adj sa'nok/n lrrtok/nsi si/v
May the Great Mother smile upon our first meeting.
lrrtok/nsi - nawm/adj sa'nok/n lrrtok/nsi - oenga/pn 'awve/adj ultxa/n

Movie (Grace)
Tsun tivam. Aylì'u ngian nì'it skepek lu.
tsun/v tam/v lì'u/n ngian/adv nì'it/adv skepek/adj lu/v
It's okay. The words, however, are a bit formal.
- tam/v - lì'u/n ngian/adv lu/v nì'it/adv nì'it/adv skepek/adj

Movie (Norm)
Zìsìto amrr ftolia ohe, slä zene fko nivume nìtxan.
zìsìt/n mrr/num ftia/v ohe/pn slä/conj zene/v fko/pn nume/v nìtxan/adv
I studied for five years, but you need to learn much.
ohe/pn ftia/v zìsìt/n mrr/num zìsìt/n slä/conj fko/pn zene/v zene/v nume/v nìtxan/adv

Movie (Neytiri)
Oeru txoa livu, ma oeyä tsmukan. Hu nawma sa'nok tivul ngeyä tirea. Oeru txoa livu.
oe/pn txoa/n lu/v ma/conj oe/pn tsmukan/n hu/adp nawm/adj sa'nok/n tul/v nga/pn tirea/n oe/pn txoa/n lu/v
Forgive me, my brother. May your spirit run with the Great Mother. Forgive me.
txoa/n oe/pn oe/pn tsmukan/n tul/v nga/pn tirea/n tul/v hu/adp - nawm/adj sa'nok/n txoa/n oe/pn
